<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PBPKO_00005> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "Perfusion-limited models are a type of physiologically based pharmacokinetic (pbpk) model that assumes that the concentration of a compound in tissues reaches equilibrium with the compound in the circulation rapidly. in perfusion-limited models, the rate of compound uptake by tissues is limited by blood flow, and the rate of compound elimination is limited by the rate of diffusion from the tissue to the blood" .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PBPKO_00005> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000117> "0000-0001-8345-1349" .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PBPKO_00005> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000117> "0000-0002-9795-5967" .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PBPKO_00005> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "perfusion limited model" .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PBPKO_00005> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#closeMatch> "http://scai.fraunhofer.de/HuPSON#SCAIVPH_00000591" .
_:genid757 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Axiom> .
_:genid757 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedSource> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PBPKO_00005> .
_:genid757 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedProperty> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> .
_:genid757 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#annotatedTarget> "Perfusion-limited models are a type of physiologically based pharmacokinetic (pbpk) model that assumes that the concentration of a compound in tissues reaches equilibrium with the compound in the circulation rapidly. in perfusion-limited models, the rate of compound uptake by tissues is limited by blood flow, and the rate of compound elimination is limited by the rate of diffusion from the tissue to the blood" .
_:genid757 <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> "https://doi.org/10.3390/nano10071267" .
