# http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PBPKO_00006
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PBPKO_00006> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PBPKO_00006> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PBPKO_00002> .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PBPKO_00006> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "Physiological parameters in pbpk modeling provide the structural framework of the model and are used to simulate the absorption, distribution, metabolism, and excretion (adme) of a substance throughout the body. these parameters include body weight, height, organ volume, cardiac output, organ blood flow, and tissue composition." .
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PBPKO_00006> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000117> "0000-0001-8345-1349" .
