<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PBPKO_00216> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "Kd in pbpk modeling refers to the dissociation constant of a compound-receptor complex, which is a measure of the affinity of the compound for its target receptor. it affects the distribution and elimination of the compound in the body. the dissociation constant (kd) is defined as the ratio of the rate constants for the forward and reverse reactions of the compound-receptor complex." .
